revision.text:
{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2012}} {{Use Australian English|date=October 2012}} {{Infobox film | name = 4 | image = 4_2007Poster.jpg | caption = US Film Poster | director = Tim Slade | producer = Joanna Buggy and Tim Slade | writer = | narrator = | starring = [[Sayaka Shoji]], [[Niki Vasilakis]], [[Cho-Liang Lin]], [[Pekka Kuusisto]] | music = | cinematography = [[Pieter de Vries]] | editing = Lindi Harrison | distributor = Vast Productions | released = {{Film date|2007}} | runtime = 88 minutes | country = Australia | language = | budget = $750,000 }} '''''4''''' is a 2007 Australian [[documentary film]] directed by [[Tim Slade (Director)|Tim Slade]] exploring [[Antonio Vivaldi]]'s ''[[The Four Seasons (Vivaldi)|The Four Seasons]]'' through the eyes of four violinists in four countries. Each musician represents a season appropriate to his or her country: [[Sayaka Shoji]] plays Spring in Japan, [[Niki Vasilakis]] plays Summer in Australia, [[Cho-Liang Lin]] plays Autumn in the United States, and [[Pekka Kuusisto]] plays Winter in Finland.
The film was nominated for two Australian Film Institute Awards, an International Documentary Association Award, as well as awards at the Banff World Television Festival. It won several awards, including a Gold HUGO in Chicago. It has sold to more than 20 international broadcasters and screened at more than 25 international film festivals.
It screened on NHK in Japan in December 2010, and on PBS stations in the USA in May 2011, and continues to sell via DVD in Australia, New Zealand and the United States, as well as via online sales.
==Box office== ''4'' took $118,270 at the box office in Australia.<ref>[http://film.vic.gov.au/resources/documents/AA4_Aust_Box_office_report.pdf ''Film Victoria - Australian Films at the Australian Box Office'']</ref> It grossed back its production budget via theatrical release, broadcast, DVD, CD Soundtrack and ancillary sales.
