{{defn|}}
{{term|action axis}}
{{defn|}}
{{term|[[actor]]}}
{{ghat|A female actor is called an '''actress'''.}}
{{defn|Any person, male or female, who portrays a {{gli|character}} in a performance.<ref>"The dramatic world can be extended to include the 'author', the 'audience' and even the 'theatre'; but these remain 'possible' surrogates, not the 'actual' referents as such" (Elam 1980, 110).</ref>}}
{{term|[[Film adaptation|adaptation]]}}
