{{term|[[film crew]]}}
{{defn|The collective term for a group of people hired by a {{gli|film production}} company for the purpose of {{gli|filmmaking|producing}} a {{gli|film}} or {{gli|motion picture}}. The crew is distinguished from the {{gli|cast}}, which is generally understood to consist solely of the {{gli|actor|actors}} who appear in front of the camera or {{gli|voice acting|provide voices}} for characters in the film, as well as from the {{gli|producer|producers}}, who own at least a portion of the production company or the film's intellectual property rights.}}
