{{term|[[Tilt (camera)|tilt]]}}
{{defn|Is a [[cinematography|cinematographic]] technique in which the [[camera]] stays in a fixed position but [[rotation|rotates]] up/down in a [[vertical direction|vertical]] [[plane (mathematics)|plane]].<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=z1Khj2gYS-QC&pg=PA76|title=Television Innovations: 50 Technological Developments : a Personal Selection|last=Howett|first=Dicky|date=2006|publisher=Kelly Publications|year=|isbn=9781903053225|location=|pages=76|language=en}}</ref> Tilting the camera results in a motion similar to someone raising or lowering their head to look up or down. It is distinguished from [[panning (camera)|panning]] in which the camera is horizontally pivoted left or right. Pan and tilt can be used simultaneously.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=Hkd5AgAAQBAJ&pg=PA175|title=Producing and Directing the Short Film and Video|last=Irving|first=David K.|last2=Rea|first2=Peter W.|date=2013-03-20|publisher=CRC Press|year=|isbn=9781136048340|location=|pages=175|language=en}}</ref> In some situations the lens itself may be tilted with respect to the fixed camera body in order to generate greater depth of focus. <ref>{{cite book | last1=Huda | first1=Anwar | title = The Art and Science of Cinema | publisher = Atlantic Publishers & Dist | date = 2004 | pages = 141 | ISBN = 9788126903481}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=Bc-9CgAAQBAJ&pg=PA54&dq=tilt+camera+movement&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiDlvTB8KjZAhUHCsAKHcjCDxkQ6AEINDAC#v=onepage&q=tilt%20camera%20movement&f=false|title=A User's Guide to the View Camera: Third Edition|last=Stone|first=Jim|date=2015-10-16|publisher=CRC Press|year=|isbn=9781317422693|location=|pages=50-54|language=en}}</ref>}}
{{term|[[timecode]]}}
{{ghat|Also '''time code'''.}}
{{defn|A sequence of numeric codes generated at regular intervals by a timing [[synchronization]] system and commonly used in {{gli|video production}} and other applications which require temporal coordination or logging of recordings or actions.}}
