{{term|[[wide release]]}}
{{defn|Is a [[Film|motion picture]] that is playing nationally. This is contrast to a film that is having premiere showings at a few cinemas , or is in [[limited release]] at selected cinemas in larger cities around the country. In the American film industry, a movie is considered by some to be a wide release when it plays in 600 cinemas or more in the United States and [[Canada]].<ref>[http://www.boxofficemojo.com/about/boxoffice.htm About Movie Box Office Tracking and Terms]. [[Box Office Mojo]]. Retrieved 2010-08-28.</ref>}}
